    • Method Detail

      • getTypename

        String getTypename()
        Returns the typename of the resulting kind of value returned by this ArgumentParser.

        Essentially, a human-friendly name for T. This typename appears in any syntax error messages that result from this parser failing to correctly produce a result.

        Parsers in ArgumentParsers establish a common format. New implementations should try to follow.

        • parsers with choices have choices separated using the '|' character (u007C)
        • parsers taking the remaining tokens have " .." appended to the end of their typename

        When syntax is generated, angle brackets (<, >) surround non-optional parsers' typenames. Parsers who have a default value, either a non-empty getDefaultToken() or getDefaultParameter(), have their typename surrounded by square brackets ([, ]). If a default token is present (and a default parameter is not present and therefore did not take priority), the typename is appended to with an equals sign '=' (u003D) followed by the default token.

        Returns:
        the typename of this ArgumentParser's resulting value type

        default Optional<String> getDefaultToken()

      • getDefaultParameter

        default Optional<T> getDefaultParameter()
        Returns a token to return should no tokens be available for consumption.

        This takes priority over getDefaultToken().

        Returns:
        a token to return should no tokens be available for consumption?

      • parse

        T parse(RawArguments args)
        Attempts to parse remaining arguments within the passed RawArguments instance into a usable value.

        Should issues occur with parsing, one should throw a ParseException to signify that something went wrong. It is considered an internal error should anything other than a ParseException be thrown from this method.

        If only one argument is consumed, it is safe to not peek through the arguments object as the object is guaranteed to always have at least one parameter available when passed to this method.

        Parameters:
        args - the RawArguments to parse
        Returns:
        a value

      • getSuggestions

        default Set<String> getSuggestions()
        Returns suggestions for tab completion.

        This can return null or an empty list to signify no suggestions.

        Returns:
        a list of suggestions for tab completion
